      <scopecontent id="aspace_14524f3896546ec4981fa5e220b2e0c4">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Papers of Samuel J. Hitchcock, 1810-1845. Includes personal papers and business papers for matters primarily taking place in New Haven, Connecticut. Personal papers document Hitchcock's private and family correspondence and finances. Business papers document Hitchcock's work with Seth Perkins Staples in the operation of their law firm Staples and Hitchcock, as well his work with the Farmington Canal Company and Hartford and New Haven Rail Road Company.</p>
      </scopecontent>
